%N A068128 Triangular numbers with sum of digits = 6.
%C A068128 1. The sequence is unbounded, as the (2*10^k +1)-th triangular number is a term. 2. The sum of the digits of triangular numbers in most cases is a triangular number. 3. Conjecture: For every triangular number T there exist infinitely many triangular numbers with sum of digits = T.
%t A068128 Select[Accumulate[Range[20000002]],Total[IntegerDigits[#]]==6&] (* _Harvey P. Dale_, Jun 05 2012 *)
